A '''toxicant''' is a type of [[poison]] that is made by humans or introduced into the environment by human activity.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cancer.gov/dictionary?cdrid=687391|title=National Cancer Institute Dictionary: definition for 'toxicant'}}</ref> This is in contrast to a [[toxin]], which is a poison produced naturally by an organism (e.g. plant, animal, insect).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cancer.gov/dictionary?CdrID=46622|title=National Cancer Institute Dictionary: definition for 'toxin'}}</ref>

==Pesticides==
Some toxicants are specifically developed to fight pests, the so-called [[pesticide]]s such as

* [[insecticide]]s to kill insects
* [[herbicides]] to kill weeds,
* food conservation products to kill micro-organisms

